# 02 Consent and DSAR

## Intent
Guarantee user control and rights handling with auditable workflows.

## Mandatory
- Consent must be granular, purpose-specific, revocable, and versioned.
- Store immutable consent records: actor, notice version, scope, timestamp, channel.
- Implement authenticated, idempotent DSAR handlers for access, export, rectification, deletion, restriction, objection.
- Log request lifecycle: received, verified, fulfilled, denied (with reason), closed.

## Behavioral Rules
- Withdrawal of consent must stop dependent processing immediately unless alternate lawful basis exists.
- DSAR outputs must exclude other users’ data and protected secrets.
- Deletion must trigger orchestration across primaries, caches, search indexes, and backups per policy.

## Release Blockers
- No user-facing consent management UI/API.
- No DSAR status/audit trail.
